    City Map with too many Goblins
    Map of 20 X 30
    from 10 to 19 map x and from 10 to 29 map y filled with Goblin's
    All Farmer's in this map has no enemy message = "Thank you for saving the City" and enemy nearby message = "Can't chat there are enemies in the city"
    Farmer Bob at (8, 0)
    Farmer Baker at (9, 0)
    Farmer Clark at (0, 8)
    Farmer Davis at (0, 9)
    SimpleHero Irwin at (0, 0)
    SimpleHero Mason at (0, 1)

    • Constructor Detail

      • CityMap

        protected CityMap()
        CityMap constructor. Uses the super class constructor to construct a Map of size 20 by 30 and GameMaster.getGameMaster(). This Map has 200 goblins, 4 farmers, and 4 heroes. All the farmers have the same info messages: "Thank you for saving the City" if there are no enemies on the map and "Can't chat there are enemies in the city" otherwise
        Adds 200 Goblins to the Map in a 20 by 10 rectangle in the bottom right corner (i.e, from x coordinate 10 to x coordinate 19 and from y coordiante 10 to y coordinate 29 should be entirely goblins):
        The following Agents are added to the Map:
        Farmer Bob at (8, 0)
        Farmer Baker at (9, 0)
        Farmer Clark at (0, 8)
        Farmer Davis at (0, 9)
        SimpleHero Irwin at (0, 0)
        SimpleHero Mason at (0, 1)
        SimpleHero Smith at (1, 1)
        SimpleHero Valdo at (1, 0)
        NOTE:
        call ArrayList.trimToSize() on Map.allAgents at the end of constructor.
